# Project Architecture

- Frontend is a static site: `public/index.html` + `main.ts` + `scss/main.scss`
- Backend is Firebase: Cloud Functions (`functions/src`) + Firestore + Hosting
- Keep source files separate from generated artifacts (`public/dist`, compiled CSS)

## State Boundaries

- Browser code should handle only UI concerns and validated form submission
- Sensitive operations (email sending, privileged logic) belong in Cloud Functions
- Firestore writes from client must stay strictly constrained by security rules

## Errors and Security

- Never expose secrets in frontend code or committed files
- Show safe, user-friendly errors in UI
- Do not leak raw backend/internal errors to users
- Validate and sanitize contact-form payloads consistently on both client and backend
